=== Pronunciation ===
[[Category:Hebrew language]]
אנושׁ / 'ĕnôsh / en-oshe'
=== Etymology ===

From {{HH|605}}; 
=== Noun ===
properly a mortal (and thus differeing from the more dignified {{HH|120}}); hence a man in general (singly or collectively). It is often unexpressed in the English Version, especially when used in apposition with another word: - another, X [blood-] thirsty, certain, chap [-man], divers, fellow, X in the flower of their age, husband, (certain, mortal) man, people, person, servant, some (X of them), + stranger, those, + their trade. It is often unexpressed in the Engl. version, especially when used in apposition with another word. Compare {{HH|376}}.